DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);
 
Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,7,1);
$y0 = random(6,16,2);

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Find the solution to the differential equation
\[ \frac{dy}{dx} + \frac{y}{$a} = 0, \]
subject to the initial conditions \( y(0)=$y0 \).

$PAR
\(y = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS(fun_cmp( "$y0*e^(-x/$a)" ) );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

Rewriting to separate variables, we get
\(\frac{dy}{dx}=-\frac1{$a}y\), so 
\[ \int \frac{dy}{y} = -\int \frac1{$a}\,dx, \]
and
\[ \ln |y| = -\frac1{$a}x+C. \]

Solving for \(y\), we have
\[ y=Ae^{-\frac1{$a}x}, \hbox{ where } A=\pm e^C. \]
Since \(y(0)=A=$y0,\) we have
\[
y=$y0 e^{-\frac1{$a}x}.
\]

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


